Package: uniEDA
Type: Package
Title: Advanced Univariate Exploratory Data Analysis Tool
Version: 0.1.0
Author: Xinze (Cynthia) Yu,  Xingchen (Annie) Hu, Rebecca Raj, Syeda Aiman Fatima, and Meagan Lacroix 
Maintainer: Meagan Lacroix <meaganlacroix@alumni.trentu.ca>
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Description: uniEDA streamlines univariate exploratory data analysis, offering detailed summaries and visual diagnostics 
    for continuous and categorical variables. The package flags potential issues (e.g., skewness, kurtosis, outliers, missing data) 
    using customizable thresholds. It generates intuitive plots like histograms and bar charts with outlier annotation. 
    Ideal for data diagnostics and transformation recommendations.
URL: https://github.com/MeaganLacroix/uniEDA
BugReports: https://github.com/MeaganLacroix/uniEDA/issues
Dependencies: R (>= 2.10)
Suggested Packages: testthat (>= 3.0.0)
